good%20thing%20is%20that%20my%20daughter%20had%20a%20life%20insurance%20policy%2C%20and%20I%20was%20the%20beneficiary.%20We%20couldn't%20have%20afforded%20what%20they%20needed%20without%20that.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20other%20people%20manage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20enough%20for%20me%20to%20get%20them%20into%20private%20schools%20and%20get%20them%20uniforms.%20The%20money%20also%20paid%20for%20my%20granddaughter's%20college%20education.%20She's%20a%20CPA%20now%20with%20a%20master's%20degree.%20My%20grandson%20didn't%20want%20to%20enroll%20in%20college%2C%20but%20he%20now%20has%20a%20wonderful%20events%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2229a982b6-12c8-4d94-b14f-3003bf809bee%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20after%20my%20husband%20died%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20all%20the%20shenanigans%20that%20went%20on%2C%20it's%20amazing%20to%20see%20that%20they're%20just%20two%20amazing%20people%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20tell%20me%20that%20I%20did%20a%20wonderful%20job%20with%20them.%20I%20say%20that%20the%20only%20wonderful%20job%20I%20did%20was%20keeping%20myself%20sane.%20Everything%20fell%20into%20place%20after%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20died%20in%202011.%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work%20around%20then.%20I%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-aging-working-at-80-no-savings-social-security-struggles-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efile%20for%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E%20soon%20after%2C%20because%20I%20couldn't%20pay%20the%20bills.%20I%20now%20earn%20%2412%20an%20hour%20working%20part-time%20as%20a%20church%20secretary%20and%20part-time%20as%20an%20editorial%20assistant.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20work%2C%20but%20I%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a50ddafc-0f9b-4128-9ffc-6f748d114043%5C%22%3EI%20want%20to%20retire%20by%2090%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20go%20to%20as%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhosted-dinner-party-every-satur